JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks are investigating fraud and corruption allegations at the Tutuka Power Station in Mpumalanga. A report, commissioned by Eskom in 2019, points to numerous lapses coupled with alleged crimes. READ: There's still a lot of corruption at Eskom - expert Eskom CEO Andre de Ruyter described it as the utility's worst-performing station. He said it was badly affected by corruption. eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones shares more details in the video above.